\b\fs24 1. INTRODUCTION\par
\b0\fs20\par
Welcome to LOKA Fleet Management System! As an Administrator, you have the highest level of access in the system. You are responsible for system configuration, user management, security oversight, and ensuring the overall integrity of the fleet management operations.\par
\par
\b Your Responsibilities:\par
\b0\par
\bullet\ Complete system administration\par
\bullet\ User account management (create, edit, deactivate)\par
\bullet\ Role and permission assignments\par
\bullet\ Department management\par
\bullet\ System configuration and settings\par
\bullet\ Audit log review and compliance\par
\bullet\ Override capabilities for all approvals\par
\bullet\ Security monitoring and incident response\par
\bullet\ Data integrity and backup coordination\par
\bullet\ Technical troubleshooting\par
\par
\b Your Access Level:\par
\b0\par
As Administrator (Level 5 - Highest), you can:\par
\bullet\ Access ALL system features\par
\bullet\ View and process ALL requests (not just assigned)\par
\bullet\ Manage ALL user accounts and roles\par
\bullet\ Access Audit Logs\par
\bullet\ Configure System Settings\par
\bullet\ Override any approval decision\par
\bullet\ View all reports and data\par
\bullet\ Perform administrative actions\par
\par
\b\fs24 2. GETTING STARTED\par
\b0\fs20\par
\b Logging In:\par
\b0\par
1. Open your web browser and go to the LOKA Fleet Management URL\par
2. Enter your administrator email address\par
3. Enter your password\par
4. Click "Login"\par
\par
\b Important Security Note:\par
\b0\par
Administrator accounts have elevated privileges. Always:\par
\bullet\ Use a strong, unique password\par
\bullet\ Log out when stepping away\par
\bullet\ Never share your credentials\par
\bullet\ Report any suspicious activity immediately\par
\par
\b Complete Navigation Menu:\par
\b0\par
\b Core Functions:\par
\b0\bullet\ Dashboard - System-wide overview\par
\bullet\ Requests - All requests in the system\par
\bullet\ Availability - Vehicle schedule calendar\par
\bullet\ Approvals - All approval queues\par
\par
\b Fleet Management:\par
\b0\bullet\ Vehicles - Complete fleet inventory\par
\bullet\ Drivers - All driver records\par
\bullet\ Maintenance - Maintenance scheduling\par
\par
\b Reports:\par
\b0\bullet\ Reports - All operational reports\par
\par
\b Administration:\par
\b0\bullet\ Users - User account management\par
\bullet\ Departments - Department management\par
\bullet\ Audit Logs - Activity tracking\par
\bullet\ Settings - System configuration\par
\par
\b\fs24 3. DASHBOARD OVERVIEW\par
\b0\fs20\par
As Administrator, your dashboard shows system-wide statistics:\par
\par
\b Statistics Cards:\par
\b0\par
\bullet\ \b My Requests\b0  - Your personal requests\par
\bullet\ \b Pending Approvals\b0  - ALL pending requests (not just assigned to you)\par
\bullet\ \b Available Vehicles\b0  - Current fleet availability\par
\bullet\ \b Available Drivers\b0  - Driver availability\par
\par
\b Vehicle Status Overview:\par
\b0\par
Complete breakdown of fleet status distribution.\par
\par
\b Recent Activity:\par
\b0\par
Shows ALL recent requests in the system (not just yours), with:\par
\bullet\ Requester name and department\par
\bullet\ Current status\par
\bullet\ Last update timestamp\par
\par
\b\fs24 4. SYSTEM ADMINISTRATION\par
\b0\fs20\par
\b Admin-Specific Features:\par
\b0\par
As Administrator, you have access to special features:\par
\par
\bullet\ \b View All Requests:\b0  Unlike other roles, you see ALL requests regardless of assignment\par
\bullet\ \b Universal Approval Access:\b0  Can approve/reject ANY request\par
\bullet\ \b Audit Trail:\b0  Full visibility of all system activities\par
\bullet\ \b User Impersonation Prevention:\b0  System tracks your admin actions separately\par
\par
\b\fs24 5. USER MANAGEMENT\par
\b0\fs20\par
\b Accessing User Management:\par
\b0\par
Go to Users from the sidebar.\par
\par
\b Viewing All Users:\par
\b0\par
See all registered users with:\par
\bullet\ Name and email address\par
\bullet\ Department assignment\par
\bullet\ Role (Requester, Approver, Motorpool, Guard, Admin)\par
\bullet\ Account status (Active/Inactive/Suspended)\par
\bullet\ Last login timestamp\par
\par
\b Filtering Users:\par
\b0\par
\bullet\ By Role - Filter specific user types\par
\bullet\ By Status - Active, Inactive\par
\bullet\ By Search - Name or email search\par
\par
\b Adding a New User:\par
\b0\par
1. Click "Add User"\par
2. Fill in required fields:\par
    - \b Full Name\b0  (required)\par
    - \b Email Address\b0  (required, must be unique)\par
    - \b Password\b0  (required, follow password policy)\par
    - \b Department\b0  (select from dropdown)\par
    - \b Role\b0  (select appropriate access level)\par
3. Click "Create User"\par
\par
\b Role Descriptions:\par
\b0\par
\bullet\ \b Requester (Level 1):\b0  Can submit vehicle requests only\par
\bullet\ \b Guard (Level 1):\b0  Can record dispatch/arrival times\par
\bullet\ \b Approver (Level 3):\b0  Can approve requests, manage vehicles/drivers\par
\bullet\ \b Motorpool Head (Level 4):\b0  Full fleet management, user management\par
\bullet\ \b Administrator (Level 5):\b0  Complete system access\par
\par
\b Editing User Accounts:\par
\b0\par
1. Click the edit (pencil) icon\par
2. Modify user details:\par
    - Update name or email\par
    - Change department assignment\par
    - Change user role\par
    - Reset password (enter new password)\par
3. Save changes\par
\par
\b Deactivating Users:\par
\b0\par
\bullet\ Click the toggle icon to activate/deactivate\par
\bullet\ Deactivated users cannot log in\par
\bullet\ Their historical data remains intact\par
\bullet\ Use for employees on extended leave or separated\par
\par
\b Important User Management Notes:\par
\b0\par
\bullet\ At least one Administrator must always exist\par
\bullet\ Cannot deactivate your own account\par
\bullet\ Password resets should be communicated securely\par
\bullet\ Role changes are logged in audit trail\par
\par
\b\fs24 6. DEPARTMENT MANAGEMENT\par
\b0\fs20\par
\b Accessing Department Management:\par
\b0\par
Go to Departments from the sidebar.\par
\par
\b Viewing Departments:\par
\b0\par
See all departments with:\par
\bullet\ Department name\par
\bullet\ Description\par
\bullet\ Member count\par
\par
\b Adding a Department:\par
\b0\par
1. Click "Add Department"\par
2. Enter department name\par
3. Add description (optional)\par
4. Save\par
\par
\b Editing Departments:\par
\b0\par
1. Click the edit icon\par
2. Update department information\par
3. Save changes\par
\par
\b Deleting Departments:\par
\b0\par
\bullet\ Departments can only be deleted if no users are assigned\par
\bullet\ Reassign users before deleting a department\par
\bullet\ Deleted departments are soft-deleted (recoverable)\par
\par
\b\fs24 7. APPROVAL AND OVERRIDE FUNCTIONS\par
\b0\fs20\par
\b Admin Approval Privileges:\par
\b0\par
As Administrator, you can:\par
\par
\bullet\ View ALL requests in the approval queue (not just assigned)\par
\bullet\ Approve or reject ANY request at ANY stage\par
\bullet\ Override previous approval decisions\par
\bullet\ Assign vehicles and drivers to any request\par
\bullet\ Cancel approved requests if necessary\par
\par
\b When to Use Override:\par
\b0\par
\bullet\ Emergency situations requiring immediate action\par
\bullet\ When designated approver is unavailable\par
\bullet\ To correct errors in the approval process\par
\bullet\ Policy violations requiring administrative intervention\par
\par
\b Override Process:\par
\b0\par
1. Navigate to the request\par
2. Use standard approval buttons\par
3. Your admin action is logged with your credentials\par
4. Add detailed notes explaining the override\par
\par
\b\fs24 8. AUDIT LOGS\par
\b0\fs20\par
\b Accessing Audit Logs:\par
\b0\par
Go to Audit Logs from the sidebar.\par
\par
\b What Audit Logs Track:\par
\b0\par
\bullet\ User logins (successful and failed)\par
\bullet\ Request creation, modifications, deletions\par
\bullet\ Approval actions (approve, reject, revision)\par
\bullet\ User account changes\par
\bullet\ Vehicle and driver assignments\par
\bullet\ System configuration changes\par
\bullet\ Administrative actions\par
\par
\b Log Information:\par
\b0\par
Each entry includes:\par
\bullet\ Timestamp\par
\bullet\ User who performed the action\par
\bullet\ Action type\par
\bullet\ Entity affected (request, user, vehicle, etc.)\par
\bullet\ Old and new values (for modifications)\par
\bullet\ IP address\par
\bullet\ User agent (browser/device)\par
\par
\b Filtering Logs:\par
\b0\par
\bullet\ By Date Range\par
\bullet\ By User\par
\bullet\ By Action Type\par
\bullet\ By Entity Type\par
\par
\b Using Audit Logs:\par
\b0\par
\bullet\ Investigate security incidents\par
\bullet\ Verify compliance with policies\par
\bullet\ Track user activity patterns\par
\bullet\ Recover lost information\par
\bullet\ Generate compliance reports\par
\par
