\b\fs24 10. SECURITY BEST PRACTICES\par
\b0\fs20\par
\b Password Management:\par
\b0\par
\bullet\ Use strong, unique passwords (12+ characters)\par
\bullet\ Change passwords regularly (every 90 days recommended)\par
\bullet\ Never share administrator credentials\par
\bullet\ Use a password manager\par
\par
\b Account Security:\par
\b0\par
\bullet\ Log out when not actively using the system\par
\bullet\ Review audit logs regularly\par
\bullet\ Deactivate accounts of separated employees promptly\par
\bullet\ Monitor failed login attempts\par
\par
\b User Management Security:\par
\b0\par
\bullet\ Assign minimum necessary role level\par
\bullet\ Regularly review user access levels\par
\bullet\ Audit active user list monthly\par
\bullet\ Remove inactive accounts\par
\par
\b Data Security:\par
\b0\par
\bullet\ Coordinate with IT for database backups\par
\bullet\ Never delete data directly from the database\par
\bullet\ Use system features for all deletions\par
\bullet\ Maintain audit trail integrity\par
\par
\b\fs24 11. TROUBLESHOOTING\par
\b0\fs20\par
\b User Cannot Log In:\par
\b0\par
1. Check if account is active (Users page)\par
2. Verify email address is correct\par
3. Reset user's password\par
4. Check for recent failed login attempts in audit log\par
\par
\b Request Stuck in Approval:\par
\b0\par
1. Check if approver is available\par
2. As admin, process the request yourself\par
3. Or reassign to a different approver\par
\par
\b Email Notifications Not Sending:\par
\b0\par
1. Check Settings > Email Queue for failed emails\par
2. Verify SMTP settings are correct\par
3. Check server error logs\par
4. Contact IT for mail server issues\par
\par
\b System Performance Issues:\par
\b0\par
1. Clear browser cache\par
2. Try a different browser\par
3. Check internet connection\par
4. Contact IT support for server-side issues\par
\par
\b Data Discrepancies:\par
\b0\par
1. Review audit logs for recent changes\par
2. Identify who made the change\par
3. Correct data if necessary\par
4. Document the correction in audit trail\par
\par
\b\fs24 12. FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS\par
\b0\fs20\par
\b Q: Can I create another Administrator account?\par
\b0 A: Yes, assign the "Admin" role when creating or editing a user. Multiple administrators are allowed.\par
\par
\b Q: How do I recover a deleted user/vehicle/request?\par
\b0 A: The system uses soft-delete. Contact IT to restore from database. Records are not permanently deleted.\par
\par
\b Q: Can I see what a specific user has done in the system?\par
\b0 A: Yes, use Audit Logs and filter by user. All their actions are recorded.\par
\par
\b Q: What if I accidentally approve the wrong request?\par
\b0 A: You can reject it immediately or edit to change vehicle/driver. Add notes explaining the correction.\par
\par
\b Q: How do I generate a report of all system activities?\par
\b0 A: Use the Audit Logs with appropriate date filters, then export.\par
\par
\b Q: Can I impersonate another user?\par
\b0 A: No, the system does not allow user impersonation for security reasons. All actions are tied to your admin account.\par
\par
\b Q: How often should I review audit logs?\par
\b0 A: Weekly review is recommended. Daily for high-security environments.\par
\par
\b Q: What happens if I'm the only Administrator and my account gets locked?\par
\b0 A: Contact IT support immediately. They can reset your account directly in the database.\par
\par
